
[1]brandish

   BRAND'ISH, v.t.

   1. To move or wave, as a weapon; to raise, and move in various
   directions; to shake or flourish; as, to brandish a sword or a cane. It
   often indicates threatening.

   2. To play with; to flourish; as, to brandish syllogisms.
